        "preview": "A R/MATLAB/Python package to perform virtual knockout experiments on single-cell gene regulatory networks. scTenifoldKnk is a machine learning workflow that performs virtual knockout experiments using single-cell RNA sequencing (scRNAseq) data from wild-type (WT) control samples as input. Constructs a single-cell gene regulatory network (scGRN) and knocks out a target gene from the adjacency matrix of the WT scGRN by setting the gene's outdegree edges to zero.",
